The paper deals with distributed computation and communication patterns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The focus on graph problems and interactive proofs suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of communication complexity and information theory suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
